Obviously not. This monster just let out a snarl and tried to crash into Sasserin. Luckily, Sasserin, although massive in size, was still relatively agile and managed to dodge just in time. However, Nisi couldn't help but scream out, and almost slipped off Sasserin's smooth scales.
"How can we kill them?" Nisi shouted.
"Target their heads!"
"This is too difficult!"
Sasserin let out a snarl and circled around, flying towards the mountain he called home. The black monster followed closely behind, but when it was attacked from behind by flames, it seemed somewhat disoriented. This monster had not yet realized it had another opponent. Sasserin slowed down, then swung his tail forcefully at the monster's head, knocking it off course, and the monster became even more disoriented.
Monsters were roaring, with a scraping sound coming from their throats, flying straight up, and spitting out something into the air. Suddenly, the surroundings became pitch black, as if the monsters were sucking in the light from the sky and replacing it with eternal darkness.
Sasarin's vision went dark, and he tried to step back, but he hit his head on a tree branch and fell to the ground. The monster seemed to know exactly where Sasarin was and flew straight towards him, bringing the dark cloud with it.
"Kael!" Tenruk shouted, flying out of the cloud and starting to circle, trying to find Nisi and Sasarin in the darkness below. "What should we do? Kael...? Kael, where are you?"
Nisi struggled to stand up. She thought she must have broken her bones, but her strange, unnatural healing ability was already starting to work. Sasarin's situation was different; he lay helpless on the ground, relying on a tree he had knocked over. Nisi tried to walk towards Sasarin, but everything was pitch black in front of her, and she could hardly see anything. There were terrifying shadows everywhere, and something was screaming in the shadows.
A terrifying whip-like tail crashed to the ground, flipping Nisi over. She noticed the tail was flailing wildly, but it seemed the monster's target wasn't her. Nisi managed to see that the monster was roaring, using its claws to frantically scratch at the shadows it had created. Something was moving quickly in the darkness, waiting for an opportunity to strike the monster.
Suddenly, a gunshot echoed through the air, and the creature froze, lying motionless on the ground. The surrounding darkness dissipated, revealing the truth. Kael stood over the creature's corpse, his rifle still in hand, panting for breath.
“That was... that was one of the strangest shadow jumps I've ever done... Tantaro Carthago...” Kael gasped for air, his eyes flashing with a dark energy. For some reason, his organic armor regained its color, and his eyes returned to their normal yellow.
It took Nic a while to understand what had happened. They all knew that Kael possessed an eerie shadow ability, but he rarely used it, as most people thought it was extremely evil and terrifying. However, Nic didn't know that Kael could use this ability in any darkness, and from Kael's reaction, he seemed just as surprised.
“Are you okay?” Nic couldn't help but ask.
“I'm fine. I killed that thing, and I'll be okay soon.” Kael looked at his "masterpiece," and that's when Thunk landed beside him, returning to his original Spast form.
Now, the creature is no longer moving, and they can take a good look at what it is. Its skin is black and shiny, covered in a sticky liquid that adheres tightly to its body. It has four wings and four legs, with long claws at the end of each leg, and two straight horns on its head.
Before Tenuk and Kael could even ask what it was, another creature let out a scream and jumped out of a nearby thicket. Just then, a familiar car crashed into the side of the creature, which slid to a stop next to Nisi. Nisi didn't hesitate, grabbing her shotgun and firing it straight at the creature's head, killing it instantly.
"Oh man...," Rettvic muttered from behind the wheel, then awkwardly turned off the engine and climbed out of the truck. "I wasn't trying to. Are you guys okay?"
"You missed all the action!" Tenuk said with a chuckle. "Where did you go?"
"You guys dropped me off," Rettvic sighed. "I've been trying to catch up... Please, what are these terrible things?"
Reytevic's question was answered by Sasarin, who had already stood up. He was covered in wounds and scratches, and looked a bit dazed, but his injuries seemed not to be serious.
"You killed the corrupted ones! Those infected creatures. When the corruption attacked your god, these beings were left behind."
"You mean... we... helped kill the terrifying monster god?" Tenuk stuttered.
"Yes, that's right. There might be more corrupted ones. But I couldn't shoot at their heads. I don't have a gun. And it's not fair, one against two, right?" Sasarin walked up to Kael and patted his head. "Thanks, little guy. You remind me of my old friend Alcardin. Only you're not as violent, and you don't have his ability to destroy the universe."
"Uh... thanks... I think..." Kael shrugged. "So, uh, did we complete the task?"
Nisi shrugged and picked up her camera, taking a few photos of the creatures that were definitely dead. Then, she drew out her favorite dagger - that beautiful Death God dagger - and began cutting one of the creature's horns, and then the other. However, just as Nisi finished cutting, the creatures suddenly started to self-combust, turning into a heap of ashes in no time. The horn she cut also turned into ashes.
"Well... it's a mixed bag... " Nisi sighed. "At least I have the photos, though?"
